{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-fill-in-the-blank-show-tsx","path":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-introductions-in-an-online-team-meeting/task-36","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"title":"Vežba 36","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">He's</span> može biti skraćenica za <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he has</span> ili <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he is</span>. Možete razumeti koji je to gledanjem u kontekst:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Ako <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he's</span> je praćeno sa glagolom u perfektu (kao <span class=\"highlighted-text\">been</span>, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">done</span> ili <span class=\"highlighted-text\">seen</span>), to znači <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he has</span>. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he's been working</span> znači <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he has been working</span>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Ako <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he's</span> je praćen pridjevom ili glagolom u prezentu (kao <span class=\"highlighted-text\">tired</span>, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">going</span> ili <span class=\"highlighted-text\">sleeping</span>), to znači <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he is</span>. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he's tired</span> znači <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he is tired</span>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Razumeti ovo pomaže vam da znate šta tačno neko misli kada kaže <span class=\"highlighted-text\">he's</span>.</p>\n</section>","instructions":"","explanation":null,"challengeType":22,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-introductions-in-an-online-team-meeting","lang":"en-US","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-introductions-in-an-online-team-meeting/task-36"},"fillInTheBlank":{"sentence":"<p>This is John, the database administrator. BLANK been here for three years.</p>","blanks":[{"answer":"He's","feedback